        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 67,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-20T23:41:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I considered it. If I have only one method, all responses have to be \u0027repeated PrefixMetadata\u0027, which I don\u0027t like for common case of fetching only one object.\n\nFetching non-inherited metadata is needed when updating it: clients would fetch it, modify it, and push it back (specifying \u0027fingerprint\u0027 to make sure it not gets accidentally overwritten).",
      "parentUuid": "a213f224_0484b81d",
